ensitisations, ILS Proceedings, 15thAnnual Conference, Addis Ababa University, Addis Ababa; 2003</ref>\n#Computer Networks as Mass Media: Exploring Possibilities of Computer Initiatives in TEFL in Ethiopia (Co-auth: Demisse T.), ILS Proceedings, 15thAnnual Conference, Addis Ababa University, Addis Ababa; 2003<ref>Computer Networks as Mass Media: Exploring Possibilities of Computer Initiatives in TEFL in Ethiopia (Co-auth: Demisse T.), ILS Proceedings, 15thAnnual Conference, Addis Ababa University, Addis Ababa; 2003</ref>\n#Towards ESP In Ethiopia: A 3D English Language Needs Survey, Proceedings of 2ndInterdisciplinary Conference English Language Teaching, Unity University, Addis Ababa; April 2003<ref>Towards ESP In Ethiopia: A 3D English Language Needs Survey, Proceedings of 2ndInterdisciplinary Conference English Language Teaching, Unity University, Addis Ababa; April 2003.</ref>\n#Cultural Content and Foreign Language Acquisition: A Case for Paradigm Shift in Ethiopia, Annual OSSREA Conference, Organization for Social Sciences Research in Eastern and Southern Africa; Addis Ababa June 2003<ref>Cultural Content and Foreign Language Acquisition: A Case for Paradigm Shift in Ethiopia, Annual OSSREA Conference, Organization for Social Sciences Research in Eastern and Southern Africa; Addis Ababa June 2003.</ref>\n#Woman Rights Education, Literacy Online Journal, Pennsylvania<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.literacyonline.org/products/ili/webdocs/baharul.html|title=Woman Rights Education, Literacy Online Journal, Pennsylvania See|website=Literacyonline.org}}</ref>\n#Open & Distance education for Displaced Persons : An Avenue to social Welfare, Open & Distance Education, Ed. Mukhopadhya, M & M. Parhar, New Delhi 1997<ref>Open & Distance education for Displaced Persons : An Avenue to social Welfare, Open & Distance Education, Ed. Mukhopadhya, M & M. Parhar, New Delhi 1997</ref>\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nFile:Bahrul Islam.JPG|Baharul Islam Speaking at Bangkok Inter-Cultural Conference 2008\nFile:With Prof Michael J Sandel at Harvard University.jpg|Prof Baharul Islam with Prof [[Michael J. Sandel]] at [[Harvard Business School]] during the GLOCOLL Class (July 2013)\nFile:Dr_Baharul_Islam_Receiving_The_DIT_Memento.JPG|Baharul Islam being handed over a Dept of IT memento at a Govt of India function at Guwahati (India) Feb 2010\nFile:Prof Baharul Islam at the African Economic Conference 2009, UNECA, Addis Ababa.jpg|Prof Baharul Islam at the African Economic Conference 2009, [[United Nations Economic Commission for Africa]], Addis Ababa\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Emergency management#Communicating and incident assessment]]\n* [[Karimganj]]\n* [[List of Aligarh Muslim University alumni]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Islam, K. M. Baharul}}\n[[Category:Scholars from Assam]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Aligarh Muslim University alumni]]\n[[Category:Assam University alumni]]\n[[Category:Tezpur University alumni]]\n[[Category:Asian Institute of Technology alumni]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Strathclyde]]\n[[Category:Gauhati University alumni]]\n[[Category:Asian Institute of Technology]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Like resume|date=April 2020}}\n{{Third-party|date=April 2020}}\n}}\n{{EngvarB|date=February 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2017}}\n{{Infobox academic\n| honorific_prefix   = Professor\n| name               = K M Baharul Islam\n| honorific_suffix   = FRAS\n| native_name        = \n| native_name_lang   = Syllheti\n| image              = Prof Bahar.jpg\n| image_size         = \n| alt                = \n| caption            = Islam speaking at the Media and Public Policy Conf at IIM Kashipur, India on 21 January 2016\n| birth_name         = <!-- Use only if different from full/othernames -->\n| birth_date         = <!-- {{birth date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD}}  -->\n| death_date         = <!-- {{d